               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008109079">
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharḥ-i Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_57-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="338r"/>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21933">Sharḥ-i Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21933">شرح دیوان حافظ</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله الرحمن ال رحیم. الا من حرف تنبیه یا حرف ندا ایها وصله</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">این چند ابیات را خواجه در مدح عماد الدین محمود کفته اند وتمامت این نسخۀ اخیار الاسرار در زمانۀ او شده است لهذا خاتمه الکتاب بنام او بقلم مشکین رقم نکارش فرموده اند</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>On ff337v-8r, there is an extremely long colophon that states that the commentary was begun on the 15th Ramaḍān 1120 and finished on 19th Dhū 'l-Qaʿdah 1120AH. The handwriting in this part of the manuscript is so poor it is very difficult to read. </p>
                        <p>Between ff339r-343r, there is an index of poems. </p>
                        <p>On f0v, a European hand has written out a select index reference of 10 poems. </p>
                     </note>
                     <decoNote>There is a large blue and gold headpiece on f1v with a floral design, inside which Jones has signed his name. </decoNote>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
